<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
New record for Greece. One specimen, Elafonisi, Crete, 
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="35.272415">35°16'20.7&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="23.53775">23°32'15.9&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 1 m depth, fine sand, collected in the framework of the MEDCORE project (unpublished data from 
<bibRefCitation author="Papageorgiou, Nafsika" journalOrPublisher="Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="643 - 653" title="Multicausal environmental severity: A flexible framework for microtidal sandy beaches and the role of polychaetes as an indicator taxon" volume="70" year="2006">Papageorgiou et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
). Literature used for identification: 
<bibRefCitation author="Miura, T." journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1019 - 1057" title="Lumbrineridae (Annelides Polychetes) abyssaux recoltes au cours de campagnes du Centre Oceanologique de Bretagne dans l'Atlantique et la Mediterranee" volume="2" year="1980">Miura (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravina, M. F." journalOrPublisher="Animalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="149 - 155" title="Lumbrineridesneogesae Miura, 1980, un Lumbrineridae (Annelida, Polichaeta) nuovo per il Mediterraneo" volume="18" year="1991">Gravina and Cantone (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. In the Mediterranean also known from Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Gravina, M. F." journalOrPublisher="Animalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="149 - 155" title="Lumbrineridesneogesae Miura, 1980, un Lumbrineridae (Annelida, Polichaeta) nuovo per il Mediterraneo" volume="18" year="1991">Gravina and Cantone 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Originally described from South Africa.
</paragraph>
